      "author": "bennettnate5",
      "points": null,
      "story_text": null,
      "comment_text": "Yes, you have that right. By mapping memory to the page at index zero (the page a &#x27;null&#x27; pointer would point to), an attacker can leverage a null dereference to achieve much more interesting&#x2F;dangerous outcomes than just a crash.",
      "num_comments": null,
