      "author": "shetty",
      "points": 2,
      "story_text": "A while back I invited friends for a Saturday game night. But instead of the usual board games, I decided to build a treasure hunt &#x2F; escape room challenge for them to play. Several of my friends are developers, so i wanted to have some form of coding as part of the game. The first clue was a long string of numbers with embedded patterns that was somewhat obvious to the naked eye, but wasn&#x27;t easy to extract with a pen and paper, forcing them to code :). Anyway a few clues and few hours later there was a winning group.\nI was initially hesitant, but decided to productionize a version of the virtual room, sans the coding sections and certain parts simplified. I have a lot of different clue ideas, but wanted to release an MVP first. The game is setup to be primarily laptop friendly. \nFeel free to leave feedback at hello@cluescall.com",
